===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|yomi=k|はか}}

From {{inh|ja|ojp|sort=はか|-}}, from {{inh|ja|jpx-pro|sort=はか|*paka}}. First attested in the ''{{w|Nihon Shoki}}'' of 720 {{CE}}.<ref name="KDJ2">{{R:Nihon Kokugo Daijiten 2|墓}}</ref>

Ultimate derivation {{unk|ja|nocap=1|sort=はか}}. One possibility is that the final ''ka'' may be {{ja-r|処|-か|pos=suffix denoting place}}, as in the term {{ja-r|住み処|すみか|[[dwelling]], [[home]], [[abode]]|lit=living place}}.

